################################################################################
#     Basic class for monitoring jobs in the LMS
################################################################################

This class can be used in own scripts to receive the published measurements
(InfluxDBRouter ZeroMQ publisher) and react on attributes of the measurements

The example configuration file contains all essential options in the DEFAULT
section. In order to write a own tool, you can define addtional section in
configuration file. The configuration object is available at self.config .

For use in own scripts:
#/usr/bin/env python
from JobMonitor import JobMonitor

class OwnMonitor(Jobmonitor):
    def start(self):
        print("I do something at start")
    def stop(self):
        print("I should stop")
    def update(self):
        print("Somebody requested an update?")

mon = OwnMonitor(configfile)
mon.recv_loop()
